title: For Sale:  Elevation Quadrant M9 - Standard
postcontent:
Elevation Quadrant M9 - Standard  $300 OBO

Elevation Quadrant, M9, is used for the indirect laying of tank guns in elevation.  It is standard fire Control equipment for Light Tank, T24, Medium Tanks, M4, including those with a 76mm gun, and Medium Tanks T23E3, T25, and T26.  Heavy Tanks, M6 and M6A1, and Gun Motor Carriages, M10, M10A1. M18, and T71.  The adoption of this instrument has eliminated the necessity for the gunner’s quadrant, which is inconvenient for use in a tank.

The instrument, contained in a metal casting, has an elevation mechanism, scale, and micrometer.  The unit is screwed firmly to a tank mount.  It is installed on the gunner’s side of the mount, in a position convenient for use by him.


The elevation quadrant proper contains a level vial and an index and is driven by a worm mechanism.  The worm knob contains a micrometer scale which measures 100 mils at 1-mil intervals.  As the worm knob is turned, it moves the quadrant and the index along a scale measuring from 200 mils depression has been set to the correct 10mil indication.  By turning the micrometer scale further, the exact elevation or depression of the gun corresponds with the setting indicated on the scale and micrometer, the level bubble is centered.

title: For Sale:  AK-74 5.45x39 Rifle with three Bulgarian mags
postcontent:
Note, this is exactly like an AK47 but takes the newer round used by Warsaw Pact; 5.45mm x 39. I have plenty of places I shop that sell it for about $130 per 1,080 rounds. It is more accurate over longer distances, lesser recoil and ammo is cheaper than 7.62x39. It is also becoming more available than 7.62x39 since it has been replacing it in military service since 1974. Most AK accessories fit exactly the same ,too.
I added an ATI pistol grip and picatinny rail (that mounts via standard AK style mounting pad that is riveted to the left side of the receiver). This allows you to mount a red dot or scope, etc. The rifle has the cleaning rod, bayo lug, screw-on AK74 style compensator/flash hider. I am including THREE proper Bulgarian magazines. The stock is also black polymer and is a tad longer than the typical AK47 wooden stock according to my judgment. It fits better, IMHO, unless you are wearing plates.
I am in central Ohio. Price is cash only to an 18 year old Ohio resident. I prefer CCW Licensee. If you have more questions please feel free to ask. I have a few extra mags I can sell as well.
Plate carrier, plates, AR mags, IFAK, camelbak, pouches and EOTech are not included.

Cheers,
Mark
